Kampala
Ugandan President Museveni was in combat mood and kept on his military camouflage jacket Saturday night as he addressed the country, hours after being declared winner of the January 14 election.
As he cast his ballot earlier on Thursday, Mr Museveni was in the same military jacket, which he had also appeared in during an address two days to the election.



